Subject: Re: alternate alternators

>Are the Type IV alternators unique to our vehicles

The unique element is the pipe sending in cooling air. I know others have
grafted in alternators successfully from other vehicles and used the fan
integrated with the pulley to cool them. See here for an example using a
Vanagon housing:

http://www.shoptalkforums.com/viewtopic.php?f=1&t=136215&hilit=alternator
